39\t\n    40\t## Why This Architecture\n    41\t\n    42\t**Single EC2 + Docker 
Compose** rather than ECS/EKS:\n    43\t- One person can deploy in a day\n    44
\t- No cluster management overhead\n    45\t- The existing `Dockerfile` and `doc
ker-compose.yml` work as-is with minor additions\n    46\t- Easy SSH access for 
debugging during early production phase\n    47\t- Total cost: ~$42/month (vs $1
00+/month for ECS Fargate + ALB)\n    48\t\n    49\t**Upgrade path**: Once tradi
ng is proven in production, migrate `trading-api` and `scheduler` to ECS Fargate
without changing application code.\n    50\t\n    51\t---\n    52\t\n    53\t## 
