n   557\t\n   558\t## Environment Variables Reference\n   559\t\n   560\t| Varia
ble | Source | Description |\n   561\t|----------|--------|-------------|\n   56
2\t| `KALSHI_API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Kalshi trading API credentials |\n   5
63\t| `API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Dashboard API auth token |\n   564\t| `DASHB
OARD_API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Alias for API_KEY (internal calls) |\n   565\t
| `JWT_SECRET` | Secrets Manager (auto-generated) | JWT signing key, 64-char ran
dom |\n   566\t| `DB_HOST` | Terraform output (auto) | RDS endpoint |\n   567\t|
`DB_PORT` | user_data | `5432` |\n   568\t| `DB_NAME` | Terraform (auto) | `kals
hi_trading` |\n   569\t| `DB_USER` | Terraform (auto) | `trading_user` |\n   570
\t| `DB_PASSWORD` | Secrets Manager (auto-generated) | RDS password |\n   571\t|
`PGSSLMODE` | user_data | `require` (RDS enforces TLS) |\n   572\t| `PAPER_TRADI
NG` | user_data | `true` — **change to `false` requires Founder approval** |\n  
573\t| `KALSHI_DEMO` | optional | `1` to use Kalshi demo API instead of live |\n
  574\t| `MAX_POSITION_SIZE` | user_data | Max contracts per position (50) |\n  
575\t| `MAX_DAILY_LOSS` | user_data | Daily loss ceiling USD (200) |\n   576\t| 
`MAX_DRAWDOWN` | user_data | Max drawdown % (10) |\n   577\t| `MAX_TOTAL_EXPOSUR
E` | user_data | Max total exposure USD (500) |\n   578\t| `TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOO
K` | Secrets Manager | Slack/webhook URL for trade alerts |\n   579\t| `NODE_ENV
` | user_data | `production` |\n   580\t\n   581\t---\n   582\t\n   583\t## Sche
duler Design\n   584\t\n   585\t`run_scheduler.sh` runs `live_runner.js` every 1
0 minutes. The container replaces it:\n   586\t\n   587\t```dockerfile\n   588\t
CMD ["sh", "-c", "while true; do node strategies/live_runner.js; sleep 600; done
"]\n   589\t```\n   590\t\n   591\t- `restart: unless-stopped` in Docker Compose
handles crashes automatically\n   592\t- Logs stream to CloudWatch via `awslogs`
driver\n   593\t- Future option: AWS EventBridge Scheduler → ECS Fargate task (z
ero idle cost, no EC2 needed)\n   594\t\n   595\t---\n   596\t\n   597\t## Monit
oring\n   598\t\n   599\t### CloudWatch Metric Filter — Pipeline Failures\n   60
0\t\n   601\t```bash\n   602\taws logs put-metric-filter \\\n   603\t  --log-gro
up-name /tokenfly/trading/pipeline \\\n   604\t  --filter-name PipelineFailures 
\\\n   605\t  --filter-pattern "Pipeline FAILED" \\\n   606\t  --metric-transfor
mations \\\n   607\t    metricName=PipelineFailures,metricNamespace=Tokenfly,met
ricValue=1\n   608\t```\n   609\t\n   610\t### CloudWatch Alarm — Alert on Failu
re\n   611\t\n   612\t```bash\n   613\taws cloudwatch put-metric-alarm \\\n   61
4\t  --alarm-name tokenfly-pipeline-failure \\\n   615\t  --metric-name Pipeline
Failures \\\n   616\t  --namespace Tokenfly \\\n   617\t  --statistic Sum \\\n  
618\t  --period 600 \\\n   619\t  --threshold 1 \\\n   620\t  --comparison-opera
tor GreaterThanOrEqualToThreshold \\\n   621\t  --evaluation-periods 1 \\\n   62
2\t  --alarm-actions arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:ACCOUNT:tokenfly-alerts\n   623\t```\
n   624\t\n   625\t### Key metrics to watch\n   626\t| Metric | Threshold | Acti
on |\n   627\t|--------|-----------|--------|\n   628\t| Pipeline FAILED in logs
| Any occurrence | Page via SNS |\n   629\t| EC2 CPUUtilization | > 80% for 5 mi
n | Investigate / upgrade instance |\n   630\t| RDS FreeStorageSpace | < 2 GB | 
Expand allocated storage |\n   631\t| Monthly spend | > $48 | Budget alert fires
to email |\n   632\t\n   633\t---\n   634\t\n   635\t## Monthly Cost Estimate\n 
 636\t\n   637\t| Resource | Spec | Cost/month |\n   638\t|----------|------|---
---------|\n   639\t| EC2 t3.small | 2 vCPU, 2 GB RAM | ~$15 |\n   640\t| RDS db
.t3.micro | PostgreSQL 16, 20 GB | ~$17 |\n   641\t| EBS gp3 20 GB | EC2 root vo
lume | ~$2 |\n   642\t| Elastic IP | Static IP | ~$4 |\n   643\t| CloudWatch Log
s | ~5 GB/month | ~$3 |\n   644\t| Secrets Manager | 1 secret | ~$0.40 |\n   645
\t| Data transfer | ~10 GB out | ~$1 |\n   646\t| **Total** | | **~$42/month** |
\n   647\t\n   648\tCost alert fires at $48 (80% of $60 budget). Defined in Terr
aform.\n   649\t\n   650\t**GCP equivalent** (if preferred): `e2-small` (~$13) +
Cloud SQL `db-f1-micro` (~$10) + Cloud Logging ≈ $30/month. Same architecture, s
wap `aws_` providers for `google_` — no application code changes.\n   651\t\n   
652\t---\n   653\t\n   654\t## Security Notes\n   655\t\n   656\t1. **Network is
olation**: RDS is in private subnets — unreachable from internet. EC2 is the onl
y database client.\n   657\t2. **Secrets at rest**: API keys fetched from Secret
s Manager at boot, written to `/opt/tokenfly/.env` with `chmod 600`. Rotate by u
pdating the Secrets Manager secret and re-running `user_data.sh` (or SSHing in a
nd restarting containers).\n   658\t3. **SSH lockdown**: `allowed_cidr` variable
restricts SSH and dashboard access to a single IP. Update after deploy if your I
P changes.\n   659\t4. **Paper trading gate**: `PAPER_TRADING=true` by default. 
`live_runner.js` enforces: `const PAPER_TRADING = process.env.PAPER_TRADING !== 
\'false\'`. Flipping to live requires explicit Founder approval (consensus.md en
try #1).\n   660\t5. **IAM least-privilege**: EC2 role has only `secretsmanager:
GetSecretValue` + CloudWatch write. No admin, no S3 read, no EC2 describe.\n   6
