ToolCall(
    type='function',
    id='tool_NbR7O61AZIdusjz5izxLxL6j',
    function=FunctionBody(
        name='WriteFile',
        arguments='{"path": "/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/
eve/output/aws_deployment.md", "content": "# AWS Deployment Runbook — Kalshi Tra
ding Pipeline (ECS Fargate)\\n**Task:** T316  \\n**Author:** Eve (Infra Engineer
)  \\n**Date:** 2026-04-03\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nThis runbook deploys t
he Kalshi trading pipeline to **AWS ECS Fargate** with the following services:\\
n- `kalshi-dashboard` (port 3200) — Express API serving trading signals\\n- `kal
shi-scheduler` — Runs `live_runner.js` every 10 minutes\\n- `kalshi-monitor` — T
rading operations monitoring and alerts\\n\\n**Architecture:** ECS Fargate + ALB
+ VPC + Secrets Manager + CloudWatch Logs  \\n**Target cost:** ~$29/month (uses 
Fargate Spot for scheduler/monitor)  \\n**Security:** All secrets in AWS Secrets
Manager, no hardcoded credentials\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Architecture Diagram\\n\\n```
\\nInternet\\n   │\\n   ▼\\nALB (port 80)\\n   │\\n   └──► ECS Fargate Service: 
kalshi-dashboard (port 3200)\\n           │\\n           ├──► Task: dashboard co
ntainer (0.25 vCPU, 0.5 GB)\\n           │\\n           ├──► Task: scheduler con
tainer (Fargate Spot, 0.125 vCPU, 0.25 GB)\\n           │\\n           └──► Task
: monitor container (Fargate Spot, 0.125 vCPU, 0.25 GB)\\n\\nSecrets Manager ──►
Injected into all tasks at runtime\\nCloudWatch Logs ──► Aggregates logs from al
l containers\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Files Created\\n\\n| File | Purpose |\\n|---
---|---------|\\n| `infrastructure/trading/main.tf` | Terraform: VPC, ALB, ECS, 
Secrets Manager, CloudWatch, IAM |\\n| `infrastructure/trading/build-and-push.sh
` | Build Docker images and push to ECR |\\n| `infrastructure/trading/terraform.
tfvars.example` | Example variables (copy to `terraform.tfvars`) |\\n| `agents/b
ob/backend/Dockerfile.dashboard` | Dashboard API container image |\\n| `agents/b
ob/backend/Dockerfile.scheduler` | Scheduler container image |\\n| `agents/bob/b
ackend/Dockerfile.monitor` | Monitor container image |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Prerequi
sites\\n\\n1. AWS CLI installed and configured (`aws configure`)\\n2. Terraform 
>= 1.5 installed\\n3. Docker installed and running\\n4. IAM permissions for: EC2
, ECS, ECR, ALB, Secrets Manager, CloudWatch, IAM, Budgets\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step
1: Create Terraform State Bucket\\n\\n```bash\\naws s3api create-bucket \\\\\\n 
--bucket tokenfly-tf-state \\\\\\n  --region us-east-1\\n\\naws s3api put-bucket
-versioning \\\\\\n  --bucket tokenfly-tf-state \\\\\\n  --versioning-configurat
ion Status=Enabled\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 2: Configure Secrets\\n\\n```bash
\\ncd infrastructure/trading\\ncp terraform.tfvars.example terraform.tfvars\\n# 
Edit terraform.tfvars with real values\\n```\\n\\n**Required variables:**\\n- `k
alshi_api_key` — From Kalshi developer dashboard\\n- `dashboard_api_key` — Inter
nal API auth token\\n- `alert_email` — For budget alerts\\n- `allowed_cidr` — Yo
ur IP address in CIDR format (e.g., `203.0.113.42/32`)\\n\\n> ⚠️ **Never commit `
terraform.tfvars` to git.** It is already in `.gitignore`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step
3: Build and Push Docker Images\\n\\n```bash\\ncd infrastructure/trading\\nbash 
build-and-push.sh\\n```\\n\\nThis builds three images and pushes them to ECR:\\n
- `tokenfly/dashboard:latest`\\n- `tokenfly/scheduler:latest`\\n- `tokenfly/moni
tor:latest`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 4: Deploy Infrastructure\\n\\n```bash\\ncd inf
rastructure/trading\\nterraform init\\nterraform plan -var-file=terraform.tfvars
\\nterraform apply -var-file=terraform.tfvars\\n```\\n\\n**Outputs:**\\n- `dashb
oard_url` — ALB endpoint for the dashboard\\n- `ecs_cluster` — ECS cluster name\
\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step 5: Verify Deployment\\n\\n```bash\\n# Get the ALB URL\\nDA
SHBOARD_URL=$(terraform output -raw dashboard_url)\\n\\n# Health check\\ncurl -s
\\"$DASHBOARD_URL/health\\"\\n# Expected: {\\"status\\":\\"ok\\",...}\\n\\n# Che
ck ECS services\\naws ecs describe-services \\\\\\n  --cluster tokenfly-trading 
\\\\\\n  --services dashboard scheduler monitor\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Security 
Checklist\\n\\n- [x] `PAPER_TRADING=true` hardcoded in all task definitions and 
Dockerfiles\\n- [x] `KALSHI_API_KEY` and `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` sourced from AWS Se
crets Manager\\n- [x] No secrets in environment files or source code\\n- [x] ALB
ingress restricted to `allowed_cidr`\\n- [x] ECS tasks run in public subnets wit
h security group isolation\\n- [x] IAM least-privilege: ECS task execution role 
has only ECR pull + Secrets Manager read\\n- [x] Budget alert at $32 (80% of $40
/month limit)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Cost Breakdown (Estimated)\\n\\n| Resource | Spec
| Cost/month |\\n|----------|------|------------|\\n| ALB | 1 application load b
alancer | ~$16 |\\n| Dashboard (Fargate) | 0.25 vCPU, 0.5 GB | ~$9 |\\n| Schedul
er (Fargate Spot) | 0.125 vCPU, 0.25 GB | ~$1.50 |\\n| Monitor (Fargate Spot) | 
0.125 vCPU, 0.25 GB | ~$1.50 |\\n| CloudWatch Logs | ~2 GB/month | ~$1 |\\n| Sec
rets Manager | 1 secret | ~$0.40 |\\n| **Total** | | **~$29/month** |\\n\\n---\\
n\\n## Rollback\\n\\n```bash\\n# Scale services to zero (preserves state)\\naws 
ecs update-service --cluster tokenfly-trading --service dashboard --desired-coun
t 0\\naws ecs update-service --cluster tokenfly-trading --service scheduler --de
sired-count 0\\naws ecs update-service --cluster tokenfly-trading --service moni
tor --desired-count 0\\n\\n# Destroy all infrastructure\\ncd infrastructure/trad
ing\\nterraform destroy -var-file=terraform.tfvars\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Notes\
\n\\n- This deployment uses **ECS Fargate** as specified in Task T316 (not EC2 +
Docker Compose).\\n- Fargate Spot is used for scheduler and monitor to hit the ~
$29/month target.\\n- The dashboard runs on regular Fargate for availability.\\n
- All images are stored in ECR and referenced dynamically in Terraform.\\n- If K
alshi API credentials are not yet available (Task T236 blocker), the infrastruct
ure can still be deployed, but the scheduler will use mock fallback data until c
redentials are added to Secrets Manager.\\n"}'
    ),
    extras=None
)
